---
description: Defines standardized folder structure for Next.js pages with co-located components, tRPC routers, mutations, queries, schemas, and constants to ensure consistent organization and maintainability while promoting feature isolation and shared code placement in _features directory
globs: src/app/**/*
alwaysApply: true
---

Page Structure:

- Use `page.tsx` for main page component
- Create `_components/` for page-specific components
- Create `_trpc/` for tRPC routers and queries
- Create `_server/` for non-tRPC server code
  - `_queries/` for direct server queries
  - `_mutations/` for server actions
- Create `_schemas/` for validation schemas
- Create `_constants/` for page constants
- Use `[id]/` for dynamic route segments

Code Isolation:

- Keep page-specific code within page folder
- Co-locate related functionality together
- Use underscore prefix for implementation folders
- Group all page logic in single directory

Shared Resources:

- Place shared code in `src/app/_features/`
- Use feature-based organization for shared logic
- Move reusable components to `_features/`
- Share common utilities across features

Example Structure:

```
src/app/admin/reviews/
├── page.tsx
├── _components/
│   ├── reviews-table.tsx
│   └── reviews-table-action-dropdown.tsx
├── _trpc/
│   ├── router.ts
│   └── _queries/
│       └── get-paginated-reviews.ts
│   └── _mutations/
│       └── update-review.ts
├── _server/
│   └── _queries/
│       └── retrieve-review.ts
│   └── _mutations_/
│       └── create-review.ts
├── _constants/
│   └── cache-tags.ts
└── [id]/
    ├── page.tsx
    ├── _components/
    ├── _server/
    │   └── _mutations/
    │       └── delete-review.ts
    └── _schemas/
        └── delete-review.ts
```
